'''"Orangies"''' [Or-an-gees] is a derogatory term used in [[Ireland]] in reference to members of the [[Protestant]] [[Unionist]] community of Northern Ireland.  It comes from the identification that Protestants have in Northern Ireland as supporters of the memory of King [[William III of England|William III]], Prince of Orange.  Orange culture in Ireland, particularly Northern Ireland, is most identified with the fraternal Protestant "[[Orange Order]]"; some [[Irish Republicans]] and supporters of [[Sinn Féin]] claim the term is only used against members of this organisation:  

"There the children play games - not of cops and robbers - or the like, but of "orangies" and Nationalists." Tina Tully, Sinn Féin

However the term is much more widely used by [[Nationalists]] and [[Catholics]] as a term of abuse to the whole Protestant, Unionist and pro-[[United Kingdom|British]] community, whether they are members of the Orange Order or not.